history.content: Your situation is what the conflict form is for. It can't be used for two classes that you're enrolled for, since this situation can't happen without the form.

Forgive me for possibly being very brain dead, I am currently waitlisted for a section of CS186 that conflicts with the sole lecture of another class that cannot be moved or dropped or swapped without me losing my seat. I cannot swap/waitlist other sections of 186. As far as I know I can only fill out an enrollment conflict form from the notification if the conflict involves two directly enrolled classes. The conflict is most likely why I am not being enrolled into the upper div since I clearly appear to have a spot. What do I do if I want to enroll the conflict anyway?
history.subject: Waitlist Conflict
